Scope — third-party GPL components
----------------------------------

The commercial licence from Softside Tech covers the bilbycast
source code only (bilbycast-edge and its sibling Softside crates:
bilbycast-srt, bilbycast-libsrt-rs, bilbycast-rist,
bilbycast-fdk-aac-rs, bilbycast-ffmpeg-video-rs). Softside does not
hold copyright in third-party libraries and cannot relicense them.

In particular, the `*-full` release variant (and any build with
`--features video-encoder-x264` or `video-encoder-x265`) bundles
libx264 and libx265, which are distributed under GPL-2.0-or-later.
Those libraries' GPL terms continue to apply to the portions of the
combined binary they cover, regardless of any commercial licence
you hold for the bilbycast source code.

Commercial customers who need to avoid GPL copyleft entirely should:

  a) Use the default release variant (no software video encoders), or
  b) Build with `video-encoder-nvenc` only — NVENC's API layer is
     LGPL-compatible and patent coverage is provided by NVIDIA at
     the hardware/driver layer, or
  c) Accept that the libx264 / libx265 portions of their deployment
     remain subject to GPL-2.0-or-later.

FFmpeg (libavcodec / libavutil / libswscale), libopus, and Fraunhofer
FDK AAC have their own licences — see NOTICE / NOTICE.full for the
full bundled-library manifest. If you are unsure whether a specific
build configuration is compatible with your intended distribution
model, email commercial@softsidetech.com before shipping.
